Butter 2. Mirin(Sweet Rice Wine) 3. Sake 4. MSD(monosodium gultamate) 5. Takana (mustard greens) 6. Kimchi 7. Edamame For Sauce 1. Soya Sauce 2. Sesame Oil.
Heat the pan: Place a large wok or frying pan over medium-high heat. 1 tablespoon of the oil and swirl to coat the pan. 2. Scramble the eggs: Add the beaten eggs and let them cook for a few seconds. Once they start to set, use a spatula to scramble them until just cooked through. Transfer the scrambled eggs to a plate. 3. Stir-fry the vegetables (optional): Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of to the pan. If using, add the diced ham or protein, white parts of the green onions, carrots, and peas. Stir-fry for 1-2 minutes, or until the vegetables are softened slightly. 4. Add the rice: Push the vegetables to the side of the pan. Add the cooked and cooled rice and break up any clumps with a spatula. Use a pressing and slicing motion with the spatula to separate the rice grains without mashing them. 5. Season and cook: Add the soy sauce, sesame oil, salt, and pepper to the rice. Stir-fry for 2-3 minutes, tossing the rice constantly to ensure even browning and heating. 6. Combine with eggs: Add the scrambled eggs back to the pan and fold them gently into the rice. Stir-fry for another minute until everything is heated through. 7. Garnish and serve: Remove from heat and garnish with the green parts of the green onions. Serve hot with your favorite side dishes.
